# BUILD

Building from source is optional, and it is not recommended for inexperienced users. 
To simply play the game follow INSTALL section of this README.

## Linux

### Requirements
- gcc (or different compatible C compiler using CC=...)
- make
- git (optional for download)

Download the repository, navigate into it and run the following make command.
```bash
    # These commands will download the repository and build it.
    # If you are downloading the repository manually use the only the make command in the root folder of the repository.

    git clone https://github.com/qubas9/Crashing-Not-Allowed.git --depth 1
    cd Crashing-Not-Allowed
    
    make PLATFORM=linux
```

The result binary (crashing-not-allowed\[version\]) will be in the root folder and all other files generated during build in the build folder. The binary needs to be in the same folder as assets folder.

```bash
    ./crashing-not-allowed
```

## Windows

### Requirements
- use [win64devkit](https://github.com/skeeto/w64devkit)
- git (optional for download)

 Download and extract win64devkit. Run w64devkit found inside the archive.
 Download this repository, navigate into it in the win64console and run the following make command.

```bash
    # Run any of these commands in the win64devkit console.
    # These commands will download the repository and build it.
    # If you are downloading the repository manually use the only the make command in the root folder of the repository.
    
    git clone https://github.com/qubas9/Crashing-Not-Allowed.git --depth 1
    cd Crashing-Not-Allowed

    make PLATFORM=windows
```

The result binary (crashing-not-allowed_\[version\].exe) will be in the root folder and all other files generated during build in the build folder. The binary needs to be in the same folder as assets folder.

```bash
    crashing-not-allowed.exe
```

To delete build files make clean can be used
```bash
    make clean
```

